                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-112-off591 t18300916-112-crimeloc594"></join>; the prisoner was a <rs id="t18300916-112-deflabel595" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-112-defend1013 t18300916-112-deflabel595"></join> of mine. On the 14th of July I received information, and when he came from dinner I asked what had become of the piece of lead which had been in the store-room - he said he knew nothing about it; I said he had better he candid and tell me the truth, or he would be made to tell it in another place - he then said one of the other men had put it there, and he had taken it out at dinner time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-112-person1016">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BARTLETT
               <interp inst="t18300916-112-person1016" type="surname" value="BARTLETT"></interp>
